# =============================================================================
# ESTValgus environment variables
# =============================================================================
#
# Quick start:
#   cp example.env .env
#   # Edit .env with your values, then:
#   docker compose up --build
#
# Dev mode (npm run dev on port 5173):
#   cp example.env frontend/.env.local
#   # Keep only the VITE_* lines in frontend/.env.local, then:
#   cd frontend && npm run dev
#
# IMPORTANT: VITE_* variables are baked into the frontend at BUILD time.
# After changing them, rebuild: docker compose up --build

# =============================================================================
# Google OAuth — "Login with Google"
# =============================================================================
#
# ESTValgus uses Google Identity Services (popup + ID token), NOT a server redirect.
# You do NOT need a public domain — localhost works for demos and viva.
#
# --- Step 1: Google Cloud project ---
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#   2. Create or select a project
#
# --- Step 2: OAuth consent screen ---
#   1. APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen
#   2. User type: External
#   3. Fill app name, support email, developer contact
#   4. While in "Testing" mode, add every Gmail that will test login under "Test users"
#      (assessors must be listed here or Google blocks login)
#
# --- Step 3: Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID ---
#   1. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create credentials → OAuth client ID
#   2. Application type: Web application
#   3. Name: e.g. "ESTValgus Local"
#
# --- Step 4: Authorized JavaScript origins (REQUIRED) ---
#   Add these exact URLs (no trailing slash):
#     http://localhost:3000     ← Docker (docker compose up)
#     http://localhost:5173     ← Vite dev server (npm run dev)
#   Do NOT use 127.0.0.1 — Google treats it as a different origin.
#   Authorized redirect URIs are optional for ESTValgus's popup/ID-token flow.
#
# --- Step 5: Copy credentials below ---
#   Client ID     → GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID and VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID (same value)
#   Client secret → GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET (backend only; optional for ID-token flow)
#
# --- Step 6: Verify ---
#   1. docker compose up --build
#   2. Open http://localhost:3000
#   3. "Login with Google" should appear (not "not configured")
#   4. If Google shows "origin not allowed", double-check Step 4 origins match your URL
#
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret

# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID must match GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID (frontend build-time variable)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# =============================================================================
# reCAPTCHA v2 — registration CAPTCHA (visible "I'm not a robot" checkbox)
# =============================================================================
#
# Full guide: docs/RECAPTCHA_SETUP.md (localhost + Render)
#
# --- Step 1: Create site ---
#   1. Go to https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin/create
#   2. Type: reCAPTCHA v2 → "I'm not a robot" Checkbox  (NOT v3 — v3 is invisible)
#   3. Domains: localhost
#      Add your Render hostname later, e.g. estvalgus-web.onrender.com
#
# --- Step 2: Copy keys ---
#   Site key   → VITE_RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY  (frontend, build-time)
#   Secret key → RECAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY     (backend only)
#
# --- Step 3: Enable ---
#   APP_RECAPTCHA_ENABLED=true
#
# --- Step 4: Rebuild frontend after changing VITE_* ---
#   docker compose up --build
#   OR for npm run dev: put VITE_RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY in frontend/.env.local
#
APP_RECAPTCHA_ENABLED=false
VITE_RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=
RECAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# Render / production frontend — API proxy target for nginx
# =============================================================================
#
# Local Docker Compose: leave unset (defaults to http://backend:8080).
# Render frontend service: set to your backend URL, e.g.
#   BACKEND_URL=https://estvalgus-api.onrender.com
# No trailing slash.
#
# BACKEND_URL=https://your-api.onrender.com

# =============================================================================
# Email / SMTP — password reset emails (Gmail or other provider)
# =============================================================================
#
# Without MAIL_USERNAME, forgot-password still works but NO email is sent.
# The reset link is printed in the backend log instead:
#   Mail not configured. Password reset link for user@example.com: http://...
#
# --- Gmail setup (recommended for demos) ---
#   1. Google Account → Security → enable 2-Step Verification
#   2. Security → App passwords → create one for "Mail"
#   3. Copy the 16-character app password (not your normal Gmail password)
#   4. Set both variables below, then restart the backend
#
# --- Frontend URL in reset links (must match where users open the shop) ---
#   Docker:     APP_FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
#   Vite dev:   APP_FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
#   Render:     APP_FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend.onrender.com
#
# --- Gmail (defaults in application.properties / docker-compose) ---
# MAIL_USERNAME = your Gmail address; MAIL_FROM can stay unset (same as username).
MAIL_USERNAME=
MAIL_PASSWORD=
# SPRING_MAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SPRING_MAIL_PORT=587
#
# --- Mailjet free SMTP (no credit card; 6,000 emails/month) ---
#   1. Sign up at https://www.mailjet.com/
#   2. Verify a sender address (Account → Sender addresses)
#   3. Account → SMTP/API settings → copy API Key + Secret Key
#   4. Set on Render backend (not frontend):
# SPRING_MAIL_HOST=in-v3.mailjet.com
# SPRING_MAIL_PORT=587
# MAIL_USERNAME=your-mailjet-api-key
# MAIL_PASSWORD=your-mailjet-secret-key
# MAIL_FROM=verified-sender@yourdomain.com
#
# --- Other SMTP provider (uncomment and change host/port) ---
# For providers where MAIL_USERNAME is not an email (SendGrid, Mailgun, etc.),
# always set MAIL_FROM to your verified sender address.
# SPRING_MAIL_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
# SPRING_MAIL_PORT=587
# MAIL_USERNAME=apikey
# MAIL_PASSWORD=your-sendgrid-api-key
# MAIL_FROM=verified-sender@yourdomain.com
